Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{100%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 1cm pieces.

Trim the @Cucumber{1/2}, then halve lengthways. Cut lengthways into roughly 1cm wide strips, then cut into 1cm pieces widthways.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%g} and pepper chunks. Fry until the mince has browned and the pepper has softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine the @Rice Vinegar{15%ml} and @Sugar for Pickling{1/2%tsp}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then add the chopped cucumber. Mix together well, then set aside to pickle.

Once the mince has browned, stir the @Ginger, Garlic & Lemongrass Puree{15%g} and @Teriyaki Sauce{100%g} into the pan.

Cook until the sauce has reduced, stirring frequently, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Taste and season with @salt and @pepper if needed. Add a splash of @water{} if it gets a little too thick.

Stir the @Chilli Flakes{1%pinch} through the stir-fry beef.

> Add less chilli flakes if you'd prefer things milder.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the sticky beef and serve with the pickled cucumber alongside. Enjoy!